# Next.js 16 + shadcn/ui Development Rules

## Layout & Spacing

### Container Pattern
- Always use the `Container` component from `@/components/container` for page-level sections
- Container includes responsive padding: `px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8`
- For custom containers, always use the same padding pattern

```tsx
// ✅ Good
import { Container } from "@/components/container"

<Container>
  <YourContent />
</Container>

// ✅ Also acceptable
<div className="container max-w-screen-2xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
  <YourContent />
</div>

// ❌ Bad - inconsistent padding
<div className="px-16">
  <YourContent />
</div>
```

### Responsive Padding
- Mobile (default): `px-4` (1rem / 16px)
- Small screens (sm: 640px+): `px-6` (1.5rem / 24px)
- Large screens (lg: 1024px+): `px-8` (2rem / 32px)

### Vertical Spacing
- Use reasonable vertical padding: `py-8`, `py-12`, `py-16`
- Avoid excessive padding like `py-32` that wastes mobile space

## Colors & Theming

### Always Use Theme Tokens
Never use hardcoded colors. Always use Tailwind theme tokens that respect light/dark mode.

```tsx
// ✅ Good - Uses theme tokens
<div className="bg-background text-foreground">
<h1 className="text-foreground">
<p className="text-muted-foreground">
<button className="bg-primary text-primary-foreground hover:bg-primary/90">

// ❌ Bad - Hardcoded colors
<div className="bg-white dark:bg-black text-black dark:text-white">
<div className="bg-zinc-50 dark:bg-zinc-900">
<button className="bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-600">
```

### Available Theme Tokens

#### Background & Text
- `bg-background` / `text-foreground` - Main background and text
- `bg-card` / `text-card-foreground` - Card backgrounds
- `bg-popover` / `text-popover-foreground` - Popover backgrounds
- `text-muted-foreground` - Secondary/muted text

#### Interactive Elements
- `bg-primary` / `text-primary-foreground` - Primary buttons/actions
- `bg-secondary` / `text-secondary-foreground` - Secondary buttons
- `bg-accent` / `text-accent-foreground` - Hover states and accents
- `bg-destructive` / `text-destructive-foreground` - Destructive actions

#### Borders & Inputs
- `border-border` - Default borders
- `border-input` - Form input borders
- `ring-ring` - Focus rings

#### State Modifiers
- Use opacity modifiers for hover states: `hover:bg-primary/90`
- Never use hardcoded hex values for hover: `hover:bg-[#383838]`

## Navigation & Links

### Next.js Link Component
Always use the `Link` component from `next/link` for both internal and external links.

```tsx
// ✅ Good - Internal link
import Link from "next/link"

<Link href="/about">About</Link>

// ✅ Good - External link
<Link
  href="https://example.com"
  target="_blank"
  rel="noopener noreferrer"
>
  External Link
</Link>

// ❌ Bad - Using <a> tag
<a href="/about">About</a>
<a href="https://example.com">External</a>
```

### Link Styling Pattern
For inline text links, use this pattern:

```tsx
<Link
  href="/path"
  className="font-medium text-foreground underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-primary"
>
  Link Text
</Link>
```

## Component Patterns

### Import Order
1. React and Next.js imports
2. Third-party libraries
3. Local components
4. Utilities and helpers
5. Types

```tsx
// ✅ Good
import { useState } from "react"
import Link from "next/link"
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"
import { Container } from "@/components/container"
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils"
import type { ComponentProps } from "./types"

// ❌ Bad - Random order
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils"
import Link from "next/link"
import type { ComponentProps } from "./types"
import { useState } from "react"
```

### Client vs Server Components
- Use Server Components by default (no "use client")
- Only add "use client" when you need:
  - React hooks (useState, useEffect, etc.)
  - Event handlers
  - Browser APIs
  - Third-party libraries that require client-side

```tsx
// ✅ Good - Server Component (default)
export function StaticContent() {
  return <div>Static content</div>
}

// ✅ Good - Client Component (when needed)
"use client"

import { useState } from "react"

export function InteractiveContent() {
  const [count, setCount] = useState(0)
  return <button onClick={() => setCount(count + 1)}>{count}</button>
}
```

## shadcn/ui Components

### Adding Components
Use Bun to add shadcn/ui components:

```bash
bunx shadcn@latest add <component-name>
```

### Component Usage
- Import from `@/components/ui/*`
- Never modify shadcn/ui component files directly
- For customization, create wrapper components

```tsx
// ✅ Good
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"

<Button variant="outline">Click me</Button>

// ✅ Good - Custom wrapper
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button"

export function PrimaryButton(props: ButtonProps) {
  return <Button variant="default" {...props} />
}
```

### Conditional Classes
Always use the `cn()` utility for conditional classes:

```tsx
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils"

// ✅ Good
<div className={cn(
  "base-classes",
  isActive && "active-classes",
  className
)}>

// ❌ Bad - String concatenation
<div className={`base-classes ${isActive ? 'active-classes' : ''} ${className}`}>
```

## Responsive Design

### Tailwind Breakpoints
- `sm:` - 640px and up
- `md:` - 768px and up
- `lg:` - 1024px and up
- `xl:` - 1280px and up
- `2xl:` - 1536px and up

### Mobile-First Approach
Always design mobile-first, then add larger breakpoints:

```tsx
// ✅ Good - Mobile first
<div className="flex flex-col md:flex-row">
<div className="text-sm md:text-base lg:text-lg">

// ❌ Bad - Desktop first
<div className="flex-row sm:flex-col">
```

## TypeScript

### Component Props
Always define prop types with TypeScript interfaces:

```tsx
// ✅ Good
interface ButtonProps {
  children: React.ReactNode
  variant?: "default" | "outline"
  onClick?: () => void
}

export function Button({ children, variant = "default", onClick }: ButtonProps) {
  // ...
}

// ❌ Bad - No types
export function Button({ children, variant, onClick }) {
  // ...
}
```

### Async/Await in Next.js 16
Remember: cookies(), headers(), and params are now async in Next.js 16

```tsx
// ✅ Good - Next.js 16
const cookieStore = await cookies()
const headersList = await headers()

// ❌ Bad - Next.js 15 syntax (doesn't work in 16)
const cookieStore = cookies()
const headersList = headers()
```

## File Organization

### Component Files
- One component per file
- Component file names should match component names in kebab-case
- Place in appropriate directory:
  - `components/ui/` - shadcn/ui components
  - `components/` - Custom reusable components
  - `app/` - Page-specific components (if not reusable)

```
components/
├── ui/           # shadcn/ui components (managed by CLI)
├── header.tsx    # Reusable components
├── footer.tsx
├── container.tsx
└── mode-toggle.tsx
```

## Package Management

### Always Use Bun
Never use npm, yarn, or pnpm in this project:

```bash
# ✅ Good
bun install
bun add <package>
bun remove <package>
bun dev
bun build

# ❌ Bad
npm install
yarn add <package>
pnpm install
```

## Performance

### Image Optimization
Always use Next.js Image component:

```tsx
// ✅ Good
import Image from "next/image"

<Image
  src="/image.png"
  alt="Description"
  width={500}
  height={300}
  priority // for above-the-fold images
/>

// ❌ Bad
<img src="/image.png" alt="Description" />
```

### Font Loading
Fonts are already configured in the root layout with Geist Sans and Geist Mono. Don't add duplicate font imports.

## Git & Commits

### What to Commit
- ✅ Source code changes
- ✅ Configuration files
- ✅ Lock files (bun.lock)

### What NOT to Commit
- ❌ .env files (use .env.example instead)
- ❌ node_modules/
- ❌ .next/
- ❌ dist/ or build/

## Summary

**Golden Rules:**
1. Use theme tokens, never hardcoded colors
2. Use responsive padding pattern: `px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8`
3. Use Container component for consistent spacing
4. Always use Link component from next/link
5. Mobile-first responsive design
6. Use Bun for all package operations
7. Server Components by default, Client Components only when needed
8. TypeScript for all component props
9. Use cn() utility for conditional classes
10. Remember Next.js 16 async APIs (cookies, headers, params)
